# IPBuilding (Cursor)

## Purpose

Replace the proprietary IPBox **hub role on the field bus** with an open central service (UDP/1001 to controllers). **Do not** target an IPBox-compatible REST API on port 30200 as the end product — northbound and product shape: see `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-05-18-gateway-architecture-design.md` (not IPBox REST clone).

**Phase 1 RE is not UDP-only:** map UDP/1001, correlate with IPBox REST (stimulus/reference only) and module HTTP; document IPBox GUI provisioning for later design of the **own** config model.

## Authoritative docs (read before deep work)

- `AGENTS.md` — current priorities and immediate tasks
- `resources_and_docs/IPBUILDING_KNOWLEDGE.md` — hardware, topology, REST API, UDP notes, install specifics

## External reference

Legacy HA integration (IPBox REST — reference only): https://github.com/markminnoye/HA-IPBuilding — future HA path follows northbound architecture decision, not IPBox clone.

## Reference topology (documented)

Two L3 domains: **thuis-LAN `192.168.1.0/24`** (internet, HA; IPBox **REST** `:30200` on one NIC) and **IPBuilding-VLAN `10.10.1.x`** (field controllers; **UDP/1001** hub `10.10.1.1` on the other NIC). Same physical IPBox, two Ethernet ports — not a separate “lab network”. Use the actual IPBox host on the home subnet from your router; older repo examples may show `192.168.0.185` from a prior segment.

| Role | IP range | Port |
|------|----------|------|
| IPBox REST (thuis-LAN 192.168.1.0/24) | *your IPBox host* (archive example: 192.168.0.185) | 30200 |
| IPBox / centrale on IPBuilding VLAN (field bus) | 10.10.1.1 | UDP/1001 to `10.10.1.x` — second NIC of same unit |
| IP200PoE / IP0200PoE relays | 10.10.1.30–10.10.1.39 | 1001 (UDP), 80 (HTTP; see knowledge §2A) |
| IP0300PoE dimmers / 0-10V | 10.10.1.40–10.10.1.49 | 1001 (UDP), 80 (HTTP; see knowledge §2B) |
| IP1100PoE inputs | 10.10.1.50–10.10.1.59 | 1001 (UDP), 80 (HTTP; see knowledge §2C) |
| Cameras | 10.10.1.70–10.10.1.79 | — |
| Barix audio modules | 10.10.1.80–10.10.1.89 | — |
| Audio switch box | 10.10.1.90–10.10.1.94 | — |
| Router (field segment) | 10.10.1.254 | — |

Full IP schema: `resources_and_docs/IPBUILDING_KNOWLEDGE.md` §12.1. Mobile UI toggle example: `http://10.10.1.1/mobile/core/actions.php?methode=protocolToggleItem&ip=<module>&ch=<ch>` (§12.1.1).

Treat IPs as configurable in code; do not hardcode secrets.

## Working style

- Prefer small, testable steps toward protocol understanding and correlation (UDP, REST, HTTP-on-module; timestamps, diffs).
- Binary captures and PDFs live under `resources_and_docs/`; do not load huge binaries into context unless analyzing a specific slice.
- This workspace enables the **wireshark-mcp** MCP (see `.cursor/mcp.json`); use it for structured reads/stats on `.pcapng` instead of pulling full captures into the chat.

## Context / tokens

- Keep replies lean; cite paths instead of pasting long knowledge sections.
- Tiered docs: `docs/context-policy.md` — pull **T1/T2** files on demand; avoid bulk-loading T3 (full pcaps, PDFs).
- **UniFi:** use the **UniFi Network MCP** for current VLANs, subnets, and switch port native assignments (`unifi_list_networks`, `unifi_get_switch_ports`); see `resources_and_docs/IPBUILDING_KNOWLEDGE.md` §3.3.
